 loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig13c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig13d.jpeg" height="837" width="1114" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig13d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig14a.jpeg" height="1718" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig14a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig14b.jpeg" height="1436" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig14b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig14c.jpeg" height="1465" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig14c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig14d.jpeg" height="1731" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig14d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14e" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig14e.jpeg" height="1447" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14e</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig14e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14f" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig14f.jpeg" height="1476" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14f</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig14f">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig15a.jpeg" height="1424" width="1638" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig15a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig15b.jpeg" height="1606" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig15b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig16a.jpeg" height="1622" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig16a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig16b.jpeg" height="1620" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig16b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig17.jpeg" height="1620" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig17" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17</span> Histologically proved cardiac lipoma in a 65-year-old woman. Axial contrast-enhanced CT image shows a fatty mass (arrow) with a distinct boundary arising from the RV side of the interventricular septum.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig17">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig18.jpeg" height="1620" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig18" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18</span> Suspected LHIAS in a 71- year-old woman. Axial contrast-enhanced CT image shows a dumbbell-shaped fatty mass (arrows) in the interatrial septum. The shape of the lesion results from sparing of the fossa ovalis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig18">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig19.jpeg" height="1800" width="1752" aria-labelledby="fig19" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19</span> Clinically diagnosed TSC in a 30-year-old man. Axial contrast-enhanced image from non–ECG-gated CT shows myocardial fat (arrows) in the interventricular septum extending to the epicardial space.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig19">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig20" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig20.jpeg" height="1767" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig20" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20</span> Clinically diagnosed TSC in a 36-year-old woman. Axial contrast-enhanced image from non–ECG-gated CT shows a small amount of linear fat (arrow) in the interventricular septum.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig20">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig21" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105519/asset/images/105519fig21.jpeg" height="1528" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig21" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 21</span> Clinically diagnosed DCM in a 51-year-old man. The DCM was proved with endocardial biopsy. Axial precontrast image from non–ECG-gated CT shows a dilated LV with linear fat (arrows) in the interventricular septum and the posterior wall of the LV.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105519&amp;id=fig21">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Shirani J, Berezowski K, Roberts WC. Quantitative measurement of normal and excessive (cor adiposum) subepicardial adipose tissue, its clinical significance, and its effect on electrocardiographic QRS voltage. <em>Am J Cardiol</em> 1995;76(5):414–418.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0002-9149(99)80116-7">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/7639175/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Quantitative+measurement+of+normal+and+excessive+%28cor+adiposum%29+subepicardial+adipose+tissue%2C+its+clinical+significance%2C+and+its+effect+on+electrocardiographic+QRS+voltage&amp;author=J+Shirani&amp;author=K+Bere